column5: Someone even shovelled it.. but bring LOTS of sand !  Channel has some very minor slush/thin ice in one spot.. ramp is totally clear thanks to wind and current from the creek.
maybe I could bring my folding boat there for a another kick at the can......I didn't boat even one muskie this year....
arent you off tuesday as well?
Wayne checks weather... high of -4C.. 35 K North wind.. snow squalls... HMMMM
no I am not off till friday the 10th 2:30  and go back to work jan 6
LOL.. usually some geese in the channel.. didn't see anything today.
Loads and loads of diving ducks Shane...

Well.. Midland Harbour was wide open at 7:50 this morning when I dropped truck #1 off for service. When I took truck #2 down at 11:20 it was pretty much frozen right across. All it took was the wind to die just a bit and wham... and it's still actually blowing pretty good. Would have been a real surprise if we had of launched at sun up this morning...
